This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it discusses the costs and benefits of IT-security measures. It may also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as honeynets are a network security tool. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the deployment of security measures. The use of modelling suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
